# JavaScript

Primary file: `draft_app.js` (monolith — extract new modules when adding substantial features).

## Patterns

- Match existing style: `var`/`let`, global functions, section comments (`// ── Section ──`)
- State: in-memory vars + `localStorage` keys prefixed `ff26_` or `dc_`
- After ranking/score changes, call `calcVORP()` then `renderAll()` (or targeted render helpers)

## Integrations

- **Sleeper:** `https://api.sleeper.app/v1` — direct browser fetch (CORS OK)
- **Supabase:** tables `user_settings`, `saved_drafts`, `league_managers`
- **Anthropic:** model `claude-sonnet-4-6`; context via `buildDraftContext()`

## Player object (runtime)

Required fields to preserve: `name`, `team`, `pos`, `customScore`, `customRank`, `vorp`, `vorpRank`, `adp`, `drafted`

## Avoid

- Adding duplicate init blocks
- Breaking Sleeper import/sync (`fetchSleeperLeague`, `startAutoSync`)
- Changing VORP baselines without noting Superflex impact (QB baseline = 16th QB)
